  "why": "The paper's fuzzer (KuK) is designed to generate realistic, human-recognizable images and explicitly constrains mutations with L∞ bounds and small per-step mutations (naturalness / plausibility). However, the method applies these constraints per-generation (population initialization and per-mutation radius) and uses crossover between mutated images (pixel exchanges), and the paper does not state an explicit mechanism that enforces similarity relative to the original seed across multiple GA iterations to prevent cumulative drift. Thus the approach enforces semantic consistency / naturalness between successive mutation steps but does not demonstrate control of cumulative distortion across the entire fuzzing run, matching the 'Medium' definition.",
